passages.text: SNOWstorm of Growth: **at,** Raise, and AI on the Horizon

SNOW posted a record $53M beat with product rev growth accelerating 6pts to 32% y/y. FY26 guidance was raised to 27% growth, though implied 2H growth (25%) remains below 1H's 29% suggesting conservatism despite expected AI tailwinds. Leading indicators were strong with RPO up 33% y/y to $6.9B and sales hiring ramping ahead of demand. We maintain SNOW as a top pick given accelerating AI adoption layered on a robust core data platform. Buy, $270PT=17x CY26E rev.

**What we liked: 1) FY26 outlook and implied 2H ramp.** FY26 product rev guidance was raised by $70M on the $53M quarterly beat and implies 27% y/y growth. The outlook implies a blended 25% growth in F2H vs 29% in F1H. **2) AI traction.** Management highlighted that AI features influenced nearly half of F2Q new logo wins and now power roughly 25% of all deployed use cases. Weekly adoption continues to climb, with 6,100 accounts using Snowflake AI features (up from 5,200 last quarter). The company has embedded AI capabilities across the full data lifecycle, from analytics to workflows and migrations. **3) F2Q results.** F2Q product rev was $1.09B (32% y/y growth) vs Street sets of 25% and represents a $53M beat over the midpt of guide, or 5.1% vs an average of 4.0% over the past 12 quarters. Non-GAAP op margin was 11.1% vs Street sets of 8.1%. **4) New product momentum.** SNOW continues to see strong uptake across its four strategic product pillars (analytics, data engineering, AI and applications, and collaboration) with F2Q feature launches outperforming expectations. The company went GA with 250 new features YTD, driving incremental revenue and reinforcing its innovation cadence.

**What we're watching: 1) Sales hiring.** Through F1H26, SNOW added 737 net S&M heads which is more than the amount added in the prior two years combined (572 added throughout FY24/25),though S&M hiring is expected to be F1H weighted. Following extensive performance management in late FY25, the company has largely completed that process and is now focused on driving rep productivity. Additional sales engineers and specialist roles have been added, with further hiring contingent on demonstrated productivity gains. **2) AI-native spending.** The AI-native cohort in aggregate spends slightly >1% of SNOW's total rev, and while OpenAI is the biggest AI-native customer, it represents <1% of total rev (though this concentration risk may grow over time as AI adoption scales).

**Our view.** We continue to favor SNOW as one of our top picks as an AI breakout play and trusted data foundation for enterprise AI strategies. We view SNOW's strong product roadmap as key enablers of AI-driven workloads and while the timing of material AI revenue impact remains uncertain, we believe there is meaningful upside to estimates in the quarters ahead as adoption accelerates. SNOW **ra**des at 14x CY26E rev on AH price vs large cap avg of 13x.

Investment Thesis / Where We DifferSnowflake is an early beneficiary of the cloud data warehousing space, and we see rapid growth sustainability on rising penetration among enterprises and potential expansion in the product offering to address adjacent workloads. We like: 1) best- in- class software growth rates; 2) significant room for profitability expansion following evidence of scale in FY21. Key risks: 1) narrowing of competitive differentiation as Redshift, Azure Synapse Analytics, and BigQuery add features/functionality; 2) more limited rev visibility vs traditional SaaS given consumption- based business model; 3) aggressive valuation premium to high- growth software peers.
Risk/Reward - 12 Month View

Base Case, \(\) 270, + 35\%\$ - Assumes FY26E/FY27E total rev growth of \(27\% /25\%\) - Assumes FY26E/FY27E gross margins of \(72\% /72\%\) - Assumes FY26E/FY27E FCF margins of \(25\% /25\%\) - PT of \(\) 270\$ implies \(17x\) FY27E revenue

Upside Scenario, \(\) 300, + 50\%\$ - Assumes FY26E/FY27E total rev growth of \(>27\% / > 25\%\) - Assumes FY26E/FY27E gross margins of \(>72\% / > 72\%\) - Assumes FY26E/FY27E FCF margins of \(>25\% / > 25\%\) - PT of \(\) 300\$ implies \(19x\) FY27E revenue

Downside Scenario, \(\) 150, - 25\%\$ - Assumes FY26E/FY27E total rev growth of \(< 27\% / < 25\%\) - Assumes FY26E/FY27E gross margins of \(< 72\% / < 72\%\) - Assumes FY26E/FY27E FCF margins of \(< 25\% / < 25\%\) - PT of \(\) 150\$ implies \(9x\) FY27E revenue

Top Material Issue(s): 1) Employee Engagement, Diversity & Inclusion: Snowflake fosters a culture of inclusion across a workforce that is diverse in many ways. Combined with its performance- based culture of individual accountability, it believes this will fuel innovation, encourage authenticity, and serve its customers as it enables every organization to become data- driven. 2) Data Security: As a data company, Snowflake understands the importance of responsibly investing in the governance and technology required to protect data in an increasingly complex, global environment.

Company Target(s): 1) Regularly stages of developing a sustainability program and has identified three high- impact areas to address in its workplace operations: a) Energy management; b) GHG emissions (Scopes 1- 3); c) Waste management solutions.
Qs to Mgmt: 1) What actions/steps are management taking to increase representation of minorities across its employee base? 2) What cost savings do you predict to have on a more diverse workforce?

Snowflake provides enterprises with highly scalable data management solutions for use cases that include data warehousing and data science. The company's offering is offered as SaaS- only and can be deployed on AWS, Azure and GCP.

Our DCF- based price target of \(\) 270\(implies a\) 17x \(multiple of FY27E total rev. Risks include: 1) sustained competitive differentiation as Redshift, Azure Synapse Analytics and BigQuery fail to add similar functionality/pricing models; 2) gross margin upside as SNOW procures infrastructure at attractive rates and benefits from scale; 3) growth upside supports the stock to the downside; 4) premium valuation.
